🚀 Playwright Test Execution – VS Code Notes
1. ▶️ Run All Tests (CLI)

Run all tests in the project:

npx playwright test

✔ Runs everything inside tests/ folder
✔ Default headless mode

2. 🎯 Run Specific Test File
npx playwright test tests/example.spec.js

✔ Useful when debugging one file

3. 🔍 Run Single Test (by name)
npx playwright test -g "login test"

✔ Runs test matching the name
✔ Works with partial names

4. 🖥️ Run in Headed Mode (UI visible)
npx playwright test --headed

✔ Opens browser
✔ Helpful for debugging UI issues

5. 🐞 Debug Mode
npx playwright test --debug

✔ Opens Playwright Inspector
✔ Step-by-step execution
✔ Slows down actions

6. ⏱️ Run in Slow Motion
npx playwright test --headed --slow-mo=1000

✔ Adds delay (1000ms) between actions
✔ Good for demo + debugging

7. 🌐 Run on Specific Browser
npx playwright test --project=chromium
npx playwright test --project=firefox
npx playwright test --project=webkit

✔ Cross-browser testing

8. 📂 Run Tests in Specific Folder
npx playwright test tests/login/

✔ Runs all tests inside folder

9. 🔁 Run Failed Tests Only
npx playwright test --last-failed

✔ Saves time in CI/CD

10. 📊 Generate HTML Report
npx playwright show-report

✔ Opens test report in browser

11. 🧪 Run via VS Code Test Explorer

✔ Install Playwright extension
✔ Click Run ▶️ / Debug 🐞 beside test

12. ⚙️ Run with Config File
npx playwright test --config=playwright.config.js

✔ Custom settings (baseURL, retries, etc.)

13. 🔄 Run in CI (GitHub Actions)

Example:

- name: Run Playwright Tests
  run: npx playwright test

✔ Used in CI/CD pipelines

14. 📸 Run with Trace Enabled
npx playwright test --trace on

✔ Helps debug failures
✔ View using:

npx playwright show-trace trace.zip
15. ⚡ Parallel Execution
npx playwright test --workers=4

✔ Runs tests faster